1
00:00:00,270 --> 00:00:01,940
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,940 --> 00:00:03,440
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:04,940
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,110 --> 00:00:08,410
(Episode 5)

5
00:00:11,650 --> 00:00:13,280
(Name, Gender, Chief Mourner)

6
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,500
(Name, Gender, Chief Mourner)

7
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,580
What's taking her so long?

8
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,720
You don't think she's hurt, do you?

9
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:54,920
Why did you let her go alone?

10
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:57,790
I was going to go with her.
I really was.

11
00:01:59,390 --> 00:02:00,590
Dan Hui.

12
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:03,730
What happened to you?

13
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:06,200
Are you okay?

14
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:07,930
You...

15
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:10,440
Did something happen to you
over there?

16
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:17,510
Dan Hui.

17
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,420
It's okay. You're okay.

18
00:02:30,890 --> 00:02:31,920
It's okay.

19
00:03:00,390 --> 00:03:01,420
Park Tae Ho.

20
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,720
Adele.

21
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:06,020
The baby.

22
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:09,160
Park Tae Ho.

23
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,730
Adele.

24
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,300
The baby.

25
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,470
Park Tae Ho.

26
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,640
Adele.

27
00:03:21,110 --> 00:03:22,110
The baby.

28
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:30,180
I'm back.

29
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,020
Were you at the market?

30
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:37,990
Yes, this is all I can do
for Dan Hui right now.

31
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:40,090
You...

32
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:44,300
Is that how you feel about Dan Hui?

33
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,300
What?

34
00:03:47,530 --> 00:03:48,530
What now?

35
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:50,840
Dan Hui, of all people?

36
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:52,540
What about her?

37
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,410
You'd better
not be putting in half effort.

38
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:02,950
Seriously? What was that?

39
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:05,980
What could you possibly make
with just this?

40
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:08,990
You should've gotten more meat
and some fish too.

41
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:11,720
Considering she just
got out of the hospital...

42
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,020
and everything she's been through,

43
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:15,130
do you really think this is enough?

44
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:18,000
It won't be a problem
if you don't eat any.

45
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:20,260
You're one to talk,
coming back empty-handed.

46
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:24,240
If you had any shame,
you wouldn't eat.

47
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,300
- Why, you...
- Hey, wait a second.

48
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:28,610
- You're asking for it.
- Yoon Jung, let go.

49
00:04:28,610 --> 00:04:32,080
- You think I failed on purpose?
- Hey, hold on.

50
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,050
- Come on. Let go.
- They'd already...

51
00:04:34,110 --> 00:04:35,550
- cleared the place!
- Let go in three.

52
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:38,120
Gosh, Dan Hui. We're sorry.

53
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:44,560
You struck out
at the hospital, right?

54
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:46,490
I'm sorry.

55
00:04:47,230 --> 00:04:49,590
I don't know how they knew,
but they got there first.

56
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,300
It's okay.

57
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:54,400
If anything,
it made the decision easier.

58
00:04:54,970 --> 00:04:57,340
Decision? What decision?

59
00:04:58,540 --> 00:04:59,640
Please watch the baby for me.

60
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:01,570
Where are you going?

61
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:03,070
To the funeral home.

62
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,910
Why?

63
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:09,580
It's time to hold the funeral.

64
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:19,790
You watch the baby.

65
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:22,290
- I'll go with Dan Hui.
- Got it.

66
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:25,130
I'll come with you.
Dan Hui, wait up!

67
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,870
Dan Hui is usually tough,
so for her to be crying like this...

68
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:34,840
Something must have happened
last night.

69
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,280
I have a bad feeling about this.

70
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:49,590
I was at the hospital all night.

71
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:52,490
They said I'm at risk of miscarriage
and need to be careful.

72
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:54,830
Dr. Do called you, didn't he?

73
00:06:01,530 --> 00:06:02,930
Aren't you worried at all?

74
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,770
This is your child
we're talking about.

75
00:06:07,210 --> 00:06:09,510
You said you wouldn't expect
anything from me.

76
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:13,710
You said all you cared about
was your child becoming the heir.

77
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,380
Then go ahead and just worry
about your own child.

78
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:23,250
So you're already ignoring my baby,
is that it?

79
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,360
This is no time to stand around.
We have to go out and...

80
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,630
What are you talking about?

81
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,330
Go lie down right now.

82
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:34,770
What's with you?

83
00:06:34,970 --> 00:06:38,370
What if running around like this
harms your baby?

84
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,540
But what if Park Tae Ho
finds the child first?

85
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,810
He won't.

86
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:45,510
They still haven't found the kid,
even with Tae Ho involved.

87
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,110
They're in hiding on purpose,

88
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:48,550
and you think they'll just show up?

89
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:51,350
The dead don't come back to life,

90
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:53,650
and no ghost is going
to bring us the child,

91
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,120
so go get some rest.

92
00:06:59,260 --> 00:07:00,260
Wait a minute.

93
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,390
Bring me the phone book.

94
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:11,200
Who are you going to call?

95
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,640
You said the dead don't come back,

96
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:15,070
so where else would she be?

97
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:17,910
The afterlife?

98
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,210
A funeral home, of course.

99
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:22,010
I'm going to call
all the funeral homes...

100
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:24,020
to see if Kim Myung Hui is there.

101
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:45,200
(The late Kim Dan Hui)

102
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:48,470
What is this?

103
00:07:49,740 --> 00:07:52,510
I die so that Myung Hui can live.

104
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:55,050
I'm sure
this is how it was meant to be.

105
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:57,250
If that's our fate,

106
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:00,890
I'm going to end my life
so hers can continue.

107
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,420
Wait. What are you talking about?

108
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,560
From this moment on,

109
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:07,530
I'll become Kim Myung Hui...

110
00:08:08,260 --> 00:08:09,990
and live out her life.

111
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,160
What?

112
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,730
Something happened
in her neighborhood, didn't it?

113
00:08:17,470 --> 00:08:18,640
What was it?

114
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,570
Why on earth are you doing this?

115
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:24,940
I...

116
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:30,210
I killed my sister.

117
00:08:32,180 --> 00:08:33,580
It's my fault she's...

118
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,930
(The late Kim Dan Hui)

119
00:08:53,570 --> 00:08:56,240
Are we just supposed
to believe that old lady?

120
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:58,710
What if she misunderstood
your sister's situation?

121
00:08:58,710 --> 00:09:00,650
I also read the letter
she left behind.

122
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:03,510
It's all true.

123
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:05,550
What...

124
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:07,550
How could they do
something like that?

125
00:09:21,130 --> 00:09:23,200
(The late Kim Dan Hui)

126
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,700
Those people took my sister
from me...

127
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,610
and the evidence
that could've brought her justice.

128
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,880
If I just sit back and do nothing,

129
00:09:34,310 --> 00:09:35,950
I could lose her child, too.

130
00:09:37,950 --> 00:09:39,120
Then let's run away.

131
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,020
We can leave
and raise the baby together.

132
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:43,650
No.

133
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:46,320
Those people aren't like us.

134
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,630
They're wealthy and powerful,

135
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,530
with the means to move the police.

136
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,370
They'll find us one way or another.

137
00:09:54,970 --> 00:09:56,000
Until they find us,

138
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,000
they'll go after the old woman
who helped my sister.

139
00:09:58,270 --> 00:10:00,570
Even the doctor who helped us
will be in trouble.

140
00:10:00,870 --> 00:10:01,870
Then...

141
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:04,880
what are you going to do
by becoming Myung Hui?

142
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:13,350
Just like she said,

143
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,350
I'm going to do everything
in my power.

144
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:19,790
The best thing to do
is try everything we can.

145
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:22,760
That's why I can't give up
and run away.

146
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:25,660
I can't live if I don't do this.

147
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:27,830
So I have no choice
but to see it through to the end.

148
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:31,540
I can't just give up and run away.

149
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,610
In my sister's place,

150
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,080
I'm going to fight
until the very end.

151
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,480
Dan Hui.

152
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:41,780
Kim Dan Hui, don't tell me...

153
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,320
If I don't fight,

154
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:53,720
I don't think I'll be able
to live with myself.

155
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:58,630
I'd have no reason to be alive.

156
00:10:59,130 --> 00:11:01,700
Dan Hui, please.

157
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:05,270
I'll fight to protect what's hers,

158
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,870
and I'll fight
until every last one of them is ruined,

159
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,480
even if it means losing my soul.

160
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,760
Dan Hui.

161
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,460
Dan Hui!

162
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,230
Dan Hui.

163
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:36,630
The orphanage
where Kim Myung Hui grew up is closed,

164
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,070
and the records from that time...

165
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:41,570
were either destroyed or scattered,

166
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:44,380
so it's hard to find her file.

167
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:49,910
What about former staff
or the other children?

168
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,080
About that...

169
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:56,490
We're looking, but it'll take time.

170
00:11:56,790 --> 00:12:00,060
It's tough to do this alone.

171
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:04,560
It would go faster with more people.

172
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:08,830
In other words, you want more money.

173
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:15,410
Follow me.

174
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,520
Unbelievable.

175
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:31,760
Did she just vanish into thin air?

176
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,020
She's obviously dead,

177
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:35,760
so why is there
no funeral record for her?

178
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:40,630
That's why we should give up.

179
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:45,270
Conserve your energy for the baby.

180
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:49,010
"For the baby's sake,
we must look harder."

181
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:50,740
"I'll search till I drop."

182
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,510
Isn't that what you should say?

183
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,950
I knew it. Waiting is useless.

184
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:57,950
Where are you going?

185
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,180
We've checked all the funeral homes.

186
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:02,550
So we'll check the orphanages next.

187
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:06,560
If there wasn't a funeral,
maybe the baby was given up.

188
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:08,360
But...

189
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,130
Seriously?

190
00:13:12,430 --> 00:13:14,930
Didn't I warn you to stay put?

191
00:13:16,430 --> 00:13:17,840
I felt cooped up,

192
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,800
so I was just getting some air.

193
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:24,040
I'm not a prisoner,
so shouldn't I be allowed that?

194
00:14:15,090 --> 00:14:17,230
How?

195
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:27,770
What? No way, this is impossible.

196
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:38,880
A ghost! It's a ghost!

197
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:41,050
Sir!

198
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:43,950
What's going on out here?

199
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:58,700
You are the lord of this chaos.

200
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:13,580
No!

201
00:15:14,990 --> 00:15:15,990
No!

202
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:19,020
What is this?

203
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:21,130
How can a dead person be here?

204
00:15:21,690 --> 00:15:22,990
You're dead.

205
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:25,260
I know for a fact you're dead!

206
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:26,630
I was.

207
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,070
I did die.

208
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:32,870
A dead woman came back
from the grave.

209
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,580
Just for you.

210
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,270
Are you...

211
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:06,040
Mr. Park Tae Ho,
the president of Adele?

212
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:15,750
Please, help me.

213
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:18,420
I don't remember anything.

214
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:47,750
Let me get this straight.

215
00:16:48,210 --> 00:16:50,950
You had an emergency delivery,

216
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:53,050
and as a result,

217
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,390
you lost your memory?

218
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:58,590
The doctor who saved me said so.

219
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:01,860
But how exactly
did this doctor save you?

220
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:03,760
Did you two know each other?

221
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,430
He said we made a deal.

222
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:09,770
He said I asked him
to fake my death.

223
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:13,470
I gave him money to get a body,
switch our identities,

224
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,040
and create a death certificate...

225
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:17,210
As if that's possible!

226
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,980
How could a single doctor...

227
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,580
get a dead body
and fake an identity?

228
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,720
Exactly.

229
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:30,090
I didn't think
it was possible either.

230
00:17:31,020 --> 00:17:33,590
I didn't trust him, so I ran away.

231
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:35,260
But then,

232
00:17:38,430 --> 00:17:41,000
a vivid memory came back to me.

233
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:48,840
Open up.

234
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,180
Enough with the whispers. Let me in!

235
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:55,310
Darn it.

236
00:17:57,710 --> 00:17:59,080
Memory loss?

237
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:00,820
She's lying about everything!

238
00:18:01,350 --> 00:18:03,350
Open the door right now!

239
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,890
Jung Ran, please calm down.

240
00:18:05,890 --> 00:18:07,830
You'll startle the baby.

241
00:18:08,890 --> 00:18:10,360
This is on you.

242
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:13,730
You should've made absolutely sure
she was dead.

243
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,400
Because of you,
she came back healthy...

244
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,800
and with a baby.

245
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:19,200
I did make sure.
At the time, she really...

246
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:22,240
looked dead to me.

247
00:18:22,710 --> 00:18:25,810
Darn it. Open the door!

248
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:28,810
Open this door!

249
00:18:31,180 --> 00:18:33,680
- Open the door!
- I can't believe this.

250
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:36,020
Get this open!

251
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:38,160
Open the door!

252
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:41,760
So, what is this clear memory...

253
00:18:41,890 --> 00:18:43,790
- Open the door.
- that came back to you?

254
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:45,260
Hey!

255
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:50,470
- Unbelievable.
- Seriously, just open the door!

256
00:18:50,470 --> 00:18:51,700
Get it open.

257
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,100
Open the door!

258
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,040
You.

259
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:04,410
What I remembered...

260
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:06,320
is about your wife.

261
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,490
What are you saying?

262
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:15,330
She warned me to stop trying
to take her place,

263
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:19,160
then threatened to kill my baby.

264
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:21,830
And she really...

265
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,640
tried to kill us.

266
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,210
Amnesia, my foot.

267
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:31,710
See?
This wretch remembers everything!

268
00:19:32,810 --> 00:19:35,580
How are you still alive?

269
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:38,320
What are you trying to pull,
crawling back here?

270
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,320
After remembering that,

271
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:47,620
I realized the doctor
had been telling the truth,

272
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:52,600
and that you were the father
of my child.

273
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:56,470
I wondered
how I could protect my child...

274
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,670
and thought about it
over and over again.

275
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:02,140
With no memory and no power,

276
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:03,810
there was only one way...

277
00:20:04,810 --> 00:20:06,280
I could go up against your wife.

278
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:10,350
You.

279
00:20:11,580 --> 00:20:14,120
You psycho. What did you just say?

280
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:16,950
Now,

281
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:19,760
the only person I can trust...

282
00:20:20,590 --> 00:20:21,960
is you.

283
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:27,430
Just as much as I trust you,

284
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,130
I hope you can trust me too.

285
00:20:30,230 --> 00:20:31,470
I do trust you.

286
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,470
More than you know.

287
00:20:37,610 --> 00:20:38,740
Don't you also...

288
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:41,810
want this child
and want to keep him safe?

289
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:46,220
Then please accept me
along with our child.

290
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:50,750
Let me live by your side
as this child's mother.

291
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:59,230
You... Hey!

292
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,740
No way. We have to go stop her.

293
00:21:08,940 --> 00:21:10,010
Get up.

294
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:11,940
Get up, now!

295
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:15,450
Unless Myung Hui
comes back from the dead,

296
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:17,080
it's useless.

297
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:18,120
So?

298
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:20,080
You're just going
to let her do this?

299
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:23,590
Dan Hui is throwing
her entire life away right now.

300
00:21:23,890 --> 00:21:27,490
How can she survive monsters
who are capable of murder?

301
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:30,560
Letting Dan Hui
throw her life away....

302
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:32,360
would be too cruel.

303
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:35,100
It may be cruel,
but it's better than dying.

304
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:36,500
Yoon Jung!

305
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,340
This is Dan Hui's way
of staying alive.

306
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,040
She went there to keep living.

307
00:21:41,740 --> 00:21:43,770
She needs her revenge to keep going.

308
00:21:43,770 --> 00:21:46,410
It's the only way to save the baby.

309
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:48,210
Come on.

310
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:50,710
There must be other ways
to get revenge.

311
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:53,050
That's what I said,

312
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:56,890
but then I realized
I couldn't think of another way.

313
00:21:58,490 --> 00:21:59,790
I was one step too late,

314
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:02,590
and the evidence
the doctor had prepared was gone.

315
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:05,300
Besides, these people have the cops
in their pocket.

316
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:09,130
What other way is there
to get justice for Myung Hui?

317
00:22:12,370 --> 00:22:14,810
Ten years ago,
when our parents died,

318
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:16,870
only Dan Hui stood by us.

319
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,910
People were saying awful things...

320
00:22:18,910 --> 00:22:20,380
that they had gone bankrupt
and died,

321
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:23,950
but Dan Hui stood up for me...

322
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:26,120
and cried with me.

323
00:22:28,050 --> 00:22:29,450
If Dan Hui says
she's going to fight,

324
00:22:30,090 --> 00:22:31,920
then I'll fight with her
until the very end.

325
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:34,060
I'll always be the last one...

326
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,890
standing in her corner.

327
00:22:41,530 --> 00:22:42,530
Darn.

328
00:22:58,150 --> 00:22:59,320
You want to live...

329
00:23:01,590 --> 00:23:03,720
as my son's mother by my side?

330
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:06,860
Call me a nanny,

331
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,990
or even a maid, as if I care.

332
00:23:09,660 --> 00:23:13,060
Just please let me be the one
to protect this child.

333
00:23:29,910 --> 00:23:31,920
Fine. All right.

334
00:23:32,450 --> 00:23:34,420
If you want the child,
then go ahead.

335
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:37,090
I'll raise him for you.

336
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:39,860
You can move into this house today.

337
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:48,900
As my son's mother.

338
00:23:49,630 --> 00:23:50,900
Honey!

339
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:03,680
You were at death's door,
and yet you came back to me.

340
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,280
Of course.

341
00:24:06,380 --> 00:24:08,020
You truly are my son.

342
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:18,060
You conniving wretch.
I'm going to kill you!

343
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:19,800
That's enough!

344
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:24,730
This is your one chance
to fix the mess you made.

345
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:27,070
Don't you ever lay
a hand on my son...

346
00:24:28,670 --> 00:24:31,910
or Myung Hui again.

347
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:35,050
That'll be better
for your own child, too.

348
00:25:29,230 --> 00:25:30,430
Don't worry.

349
00:25:31,770 --> 00:25:33,570
This is nothing.

350
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:37,940
I will protect you, no matter what.

351
00:25:40,110 --> 00:25:41,680
And I will make them pay.

352
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,110
You...

353
00:26:11,740 --> 00:26:13,480
How dare you set foot in here?

354
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,780
Finally showing your true colors,
are you?

355
00:26:16,510 --> 00:26:18,250
Are you trying to take my place now?

356
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:20,120
Don't worry.

357
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:22,190
I'm not interested
in taking your place.

358
00:26:23,390 --> 00:26:27,090
As if losing one measly room
would destroy you.

359
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:32,300
What is it you really want?

360
00:26:40,440 --> 00:26:42,110
The same thing you want most.

361
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:53,720
You were going to use your child...

362
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:57,420
to take over the entire Adele Group.

363
00:26:58,590 --> 00:27:01,690
Now that I, the thorn in your side,
survived,

364
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,730
things won't be so easy for you.

365
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:06,930
You can't mean...

366
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:08,970
That's right.

367
00:27:09,470 --> 00:27:11,740
You won't get a single thing...

368
00:27:12,970 --> 00:27:15,740
because I'm going to take away
everything you desire.

369
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:18,980
I'm going to crush the very greed...

370
00:27:18,980 --> 00:27:20,740
that made you kill my sister.

371
00:27:37,130 --> 00:27:39,630
Just like you deceived
and used my sister,

372
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:46,240
I'm going to do the same to you.

373
00:27:47,940 --> 00:27:49,640
When you're no longer
of any use to me,

374
00:27:50,810 --> 00:27:52,710
you'll have no one left
by your side.

375
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:55,680
And just like that,

376
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:58,580
you'll pay
for everything you've done.

377
00:28:11,490 --> 00:28:14,630
(2019 Adele VIP Gala)

378
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:21,840
(Year 2019)

379
00:28:21,910 --> 00:28:25,440
You know how discerning
our VIPs are, don't you?

380
00:28:26,410 --> 00:28:27,410
That's perfect.

381
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:31,080
Discerning buyers will want my name,
not just gems.

382
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:40,220
They can buy gems anywhere,

383
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,590
so I have to show...

384
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:44,290
that what I bring to the table
isn't easily replaced.

385
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:45,530
(Kim Myung Hui, Gemologist,
AD Appraisals)

386
00:28:45,530 --> 00:28:47,200
You're impressive, as always.

387
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:52,470
But don't finish up too late.

388
00:28:52,740 --> 00:28:55,940
It's Min Jun's birthday,
so you should have dinner with him.

389
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:01,880
Hey, sweetie. I just got here.

390
00:29:04,950 --> 00:29:08,380
It feels surreal to be back in Korea
after more than 20 years.

391
00:29:09,850 --> 00:29:12,690
Or maybe it's because
it's my daughter's birthday.

392
00:29:15,430 --> 00:29:17,690
Anyway, I love you, sweetheart.

393
00:29:18,230 --> 00:29:19,330
Happy birthday.

394
00:30:08,410 --> 00:30:09,410
Here.

395
00:30:14,450 --> 00:30:17,090
Ta-da. Happy birthday, Min Jun.

396
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:23,330
Happy birthday to you too,
Baek Jin Ju.

397
00:30:26,660 --> 00:30:27,660
Here you go.

398
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:30,200
Thanks.

399
00:30:33,100 --> 00:30:35,440
- That's a great photo.
- Nice, right?

400
00:30:37,710 --> 00:30:39,910
It takes great pictures, doesn't it?

401
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,150
Why don't we take one together?

402
00:30:43,810 --> 00:30:45,820
One, two, three.

403
00:30:51,250 --> 00:30:53,390
- There it is.
- Nice.

404
00:31:27,220 --> 00:31:30,190
(Pearl in Red)

405
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:32,530
Watch it, will you?

406
00:31:32,730 --> 00:31:35,130
- I could've gotten hurt.
- What's with her?

407
00:31:35,130 --> 00:31:36,970
Hey, what did you just say?

408
00:31:36,970 --> 00:31:40,000
That there are two wives
at Adele Group?

409
00:31:40,170 --> 00:31:42,070
While you've been causing trouble,

410
00:31:42,070 --> 00:31:44,170
do you have any idea
how much money Kim Myung Hui made...

411
00:31:44,370 --> 00:31:46,340
running the jewelry business?

412
00:31:46,740 --> 00:31:49,580
Chairman Park is so shortsighted.

413
00:31:49,580 --> 00:31:51,610
Instead of focusing only on jewelry,

414
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,820
you should think about Adele Group
as a whole.

415
00:31:54,150 --> 00:31:56,850
A mistress should know her place
and stick to powdering her nose.

416
00:31:56,850 --> 00:31:58,690
What's she doing
meddling in men's business?

417
00:31:58,890 --> 00:32:00,860
No matter when or how
we might have met,

418
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:02,630
I would've still fallen for you.

419
00:32:03,030 --> 00:32:04,930
- Me too.
- Kim Myung Hui!

420
00:32:04,930 --> 00:32:09,130
It's as if I've known you
for a very long time.

421
00:32:11,170 --> 00:32:13,170
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
